On Mon, Sep 7, 2009 at 18:22, Nikolai Weibull <now@bitwi.se> wrote:
> Is there a simpler way of doing the following?
>
> alias ls=3D${${(f)"$(whence -p {g,}ls)"}[1]}' --color'
>
> I need to select gls, if that=E2=80=99s what=E2=80=99s installed, otherwi=
se ls.

I ended up doing

alias ls=3D"${commands[gls]:-ls} --color"

It doesn=E2=80=99t get shorter that that, it seems.

One might want to do

alias ls=3D"${${commands[gls]##*/}:-ls}

to only get the basename.

